# 14. Longest Common Prefix

## Approach
1. Handle the edge case where the input array is empty or null by returning an empty string.
2. Assume the first string is the common prefix.
3. Iterate through the remaining strings in the array.
4. While the current string does not start with the current prefix, remove the last character from the prefix using substring().
5. If the prefix becomes empty, return an empty string since there is no common prefix.
6. After checking all strings, return the remaining prefix.

## Time Complexity
- O(n × m)

Where:
- n = Number of strings
- m = Length of the longest common prefix (or the shortest string in the worst case)

In the worst case, each character of the prefix may be removed while comparing with every string.

## Space Complexity
- O(1)

No extra data structures are used. Only a few variables are maintained.

